1. **Parses** the expression string into an AST using `ast.parse(..., mode='eval')`
2. **Walks** the tree recursively, only allowing safe numeric constants and basic arithmetic operators (`+`, `-`, `*`, `/`, `//`, `**`, `%`)
3. **Rejects** anything else (function calls, attribute access, imports, etc.)

This gives you the same convenience of evaluating arbitrary math expressions while being safe against code injection.

